  "prompt": "What is an investment banker? How can one become an investment banker?",
  "response": "An investment banker is a financial professional who helps corporations, governments, and other organizations raise capital by underwriting and issuing securities, facilitating mergers and acquisitions, and providing financial advisory services.\n\nTo become an investment banker:\n\n1. Education Requirements\n- Bachelor's degree in finance, economics, accounting, or business\n- Strong academic performance (typically GPA of 3.5 or higher)\n- Top-tier university preferred\n\n2. Skill Development\n- Advanced math and analytical skills\n- Strong communication and presentation abilities\n- Proficiency in financial modeling and Excel\n- Understanding of financial markets and economic trends\n\n3. Career Path\n- Internships during college at investment banks\n- Entry-level positions as financial analysts\n- Networking and building professional connections\n- Obtaining relevant certifications like CFA (Chartered Financial Analyst)\n\n4. Certifications\n- Series 7 and Series 79 licenses\n- Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) designation\n- Investment Banking Certification programs\n\n5. Career Progression\n- Analyst (0-2 years)\n- Associate (2-5 years)\n- Vice President\n- Director/Managing Director\n\n6. Key Skills\n- Attention to detail\n- Strong work ethic\n- Ability to work long hours\n- Excellent problem-solving capabilities\n\nCompetitive field with high earning potential but demanding work environment.",
